2
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:41,790
In association with Showbox

3
00:00:42,530 --> 00:00:45,090
A Core Contents Media Production

4
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,090
Co-produced by
Goldenthumb & Poibos

5
00:00:53,540 --> 00:00:55,630
Hey, Jung-sik?

6
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:56,880
How is it?

7
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:58,410
What do you think.

8
00:00:58,410 --> 00:01:00,750
I need it for the drama next week

9
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:02,180
so tell him it's great!

10
00:01:02,180 --> 00:01:04,020
Like Seung-chul ever listens to me.

11
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:07,320
Then make him. He's gotta do this song.

12
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,620
But the lyrics are weak, man.

13
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:13,230
What the suits say
goes. That's show biz.

14
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:15,220
Whatever, man!

15
00:01:15,390 --> 00:01:17,100
- Hold up!
- What is it?

16
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:18,230
You like this song?

17
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:19,470
Of course! Why?

18
00:01:19,470 --> 00:01:23,070
Singing about a girl to
come back to me at my age?

19
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:25,770
My heart this and tears that...

20
00:01:25,770 --> 00:01:26,770
Isn't it childish?

21
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:30,040
No! It's perfect! Don't you think?

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:30,740
It's great.

23
00:01:30,740 --> 00:01:32,980
Make your fans really
feel the song, man!

24
00:01:32,980 --> 00:01:34,980
But I don't feel anything!

25
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:38,680
You can do it, man. Feel me?

26
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,690
- It's great!
- No.

27
00:01:39,690 --> 00:01:41,680
It's not working for me.

28
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:46,090
Seung-chul! Come on!

29
00:01:46,090 --> 00:01:48,420
Get him!

30
00:01:48,530 --> 00:01:49,820
Seung-chul!

31
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,500
Yes, director.

32
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,300
I see.

33
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,570
KWON Sang-woo

34
00:01:54,570 --> 00:01:56,630
KWON Sang-woo Next Tuesday?

35
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:59,470
The song's a killer.

36
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:00,110
LEE Bo-young

37
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:02,110
LEE Bo-young Nothing but
the best from LEE Seung-chul.

38
00:02:02,110 --> 00:02:03,340
Nothing but the best
from LEE Seung-chul.

39
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:05,280
Of course.

40
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,210
LEE Beom-soo

41
00:02:06,210 --> 00:02:09,310
LEE Beom-soo
No problems whatsoever.

42
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,550
Yes, sir. Take care.

43
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:13,250
JUNG Ae-yeon, LEE
Han-wui Yes, sir. Take care.

44
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:14,690
JUNG Ae-yeon,
LEE Han-wui

45
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:16,960
See? He's asking for
the song. Do it for me?

46
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:20,480
Executive Producer KIM Gwang-soo
See? He's asking for the song. Do it for me?

47
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:24,160
You always do this to me.

48
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,870
Please?

49
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,530
So get me a good song
and I'll sing it! Damn!

50
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:27,830
Producer HONG Jung-pyo So get
me a good song and I'll sing it! Damn!

51
00:02:27,830 --> 00:02:31,740
Producer HONG Jung-pyo So get
me a good song and I'll sing it! Damn!

52
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,810
What about 'Hee-ya'?

53
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:35,440
'Hee-ya, please look at me.'

54
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,080
Give me a break.

55
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:39,710
That was a hit only cuz you sang it.

56
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:42,250
Wanna hear this song I got?

57
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:43,350
What is it?

58
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:45,750
It's off a flopped album.

59
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,950
Forget it, kid!

60
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:50,260
Let's hear it.

61
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:52,520
Really? Turn it on.

62
00:02:54,590 --> 00:03:00,430
To give you everything
and all my love...

63
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:03,340
Who wrote this? The lyrics are great.

64
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:07,030
Really? Then let's ask
them to write our lyrics.

65
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,640
Who wrote this?

66
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:12,110
Not sure. I got this off someone.

67
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:12,910
Who?

68
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:15,450
Min-chul. He used to
work for KIM Gap-sik.

69
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:17,680
Gap-sik? I know him well.

70
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:22,720
Hey, didn't he leave the biz?

71
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:23,990
Who does your friend work for now?

72
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:26,260
He left the biz, too.

73
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:27,290
What does he do?

74
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:29,490
He runs a cafe in Chung-pyung.

75
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,390
Wanna go over, Seung-chul?

76
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:34,860
- Know where it is?
- Yes.

77
00:03:34,970 --> 00:03:35,670
Lead the way.

78
00:03:35,670 --> 00:03:38,230
Director WON

79
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:43,100
Got the album?

80
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:44,440
Ah, here.

81
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,510
What's the title?

82
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:50,410
It's the second track.

83
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:52,980
Second track?

84
00:03:56,320 --> 00:04:00,530
'No one else like Thee' by Cream?

85
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:01,930
What's her real name?

86
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:06,860
I think it was EUN
Won. Yeah, that' s it.

87
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,860
Got her number?

88
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,500
She's gone.

89
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,810
Gone? To where?

90
00:04:12,810 --> 00:04:15,470
Right after KANG Chul-kyu left...

91
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:19,640
KANG knows her well?

92
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:24,610
Of course. He was
totally in love with her.

93
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:28,110
Do you have KANG's number?

94
00:04:28,890 --> 00:04:30,750
- He died.
- He's dead?

95
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:32,120
When?

96
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:35,620
About a month after
he married off EUN Won.

97
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,760
Mr. KANG!

98
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:42,330
What was the name of his show?

99
00:04:42,430 --> 00:04:44,400
'Ugly Ducklings in Love'.

100
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,740
Yeah, that's it!

101
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:49,940
He married off the woman he loved?

102
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:52,810
- What does that mean?
- Well...

103
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:57,050
Tell us what happened.

104
00:04:57,680 --> 00:05:00,410
It's a long story.

105
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,130
Hi, Chul-kyu!

106
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:08,220
KANG said he saw stars

107
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,590
when he first met Cream.

108
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:11,580
Why you little punk!

109
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,030
Like he'd been slapped
on the back of his head.

110
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:23,260
He said it was love
at first sight.

111
00:06:24,170 --> 00:06:26,100
Without even talking to her.

112
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:28,800
I asked,

113
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:31,770
'Shouldn't you at least
say a few words, first? '

114
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,470
Then he said...

115
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:38,370
If you need words,
then how can mutes love?

116
00:06:52,260 --> 00:06:55,700
How did you know my name?

117
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:59,930
Isn't it a waste living
in this big place alone?

118
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:04,740
Want me to live with you?

119
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:25,400
Think of a name for me,
and I'll make one for you.

120
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,490
We can't change our names.

121
00:07:28,370 --> 00:07:29,390
Why not?

122
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:32,870
Her name is Cream
and my name is K.

123
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,770
She was cold like ice cream,

124
00:07:35,770 --> 00:07:38,580
- but also sweet like ice
cream. - The curtains won't do.

125
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:39,780
We're changing everything.

126
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:42,370
And she was
soft like ice cream.

127
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:48,680
And I'm not A, B, C,
D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K...

128
00:07:49,050 --> 00:07:50,750
But just K.

129
00:08:04,570 --> 00:08:06,700
We had a lot in common.

130
00:08:07,110 --> 00:08:11,130
We were the same age.
We both liked noodles.

131
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:15,810
We loved listening to
music on rainy days.

132
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,710
We loved coffee.

133
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:24,490
We hated school.

134
00:08:28,990 --> 00:08:30,790
She liked me.

135
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,800
And I liked her.

136
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,870
And we were both orphans.

137
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,310
Prison and love...

138
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:46,180
Once you're stuck,
you can't get out.

139
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:54,340
I fell in love with Cream.

140
00:08:57,320 --> 00:09:00,160
Even the very air she breathed.

141
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:09,570
Romeo must've been so worried...

142
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:14,600
Ioving Juliet, but
afraid he might lose her.

143
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:22,780
Why did he drink the poison?

144
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:27,350
Perhaps he knew.

145
00:09:28,590 --> 00:09:31,160
To love someone

146
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:33,390
- is to give her
everything. - I'll visit often.

147
00:09:36,230 --> 00:09:42,900
I received so much from her
like the catcher who gets the ball.

148
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:47,270
Love was like dry ice.
Sometimes cold, sometimes hot.

149
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:48,330
Wait!

150
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:50,270
Cream was so loveable.

151
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:58,040
But I couldn't tell her
that I loved her.

152
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:06,690
Cuz I had cancer cells in me
ready to strike at any time.

153
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:15,200
More than Blue

154
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,170
Thank you, Mr. KIM.

155
00:10:54,170 --> 00:10:57,640
It's the least I can do.

156
00:10:57,640 --> 00:11:01,010
Writers need to eat well
to do all that thinking.

157
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:06,550
Have some soup with the
Kimbap and chew carefully.

158
00:11:06,550 --> 00:11:08,650
Is this your new singer?

159
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:15,080
Greet them, girl. They're
the best writers in SBC.

160
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:20,400
Hello, I'm Cat Girl. I
promise to sing my heart out.

161
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,590
Damn right you should.

162
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,940
Great outfit.

163
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:28,030
It's a new concept. She's a cat.

164
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:30,340
It's Cat Girl.

165
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:34,810
This gal's got brains.

166
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:37,920
She's a student at Seoul University.

167
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,580
Really?

168
00:11:40,290 --> 00:11:42,920
It's Seoul University of Arts.

169
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,950
Who's side are you on?

170
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:47,730
You could get in trouble for
lying about schools these days.

171
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:52,230
If you're so holy, go be a cop instead.

172
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:53,290
Sorry.

173
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,970
Mr. Kang!

174
00:11:58,070 --> 00:11:58,970
How are you?

175
00:11:58,970 --> 00:12:03,170
Here's Seung-chul's
new album. It's deep.

176
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:06,780
- It's a sure hit.
- I'm sure it's great.

177
00:12:06,780 --> 00:12:07,850
- Say hi.
- Hello.

178
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:09,110
Call me K.

179
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,480
Let's go for drinks some time.

180
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,210
- Sounds great.
- Bye.

181
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:17,090
Seoul Univ. of Arts. Same difference.

182
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:18,390
That's right.

183
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:19,820
Did you eat, sir?

184
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:21,830
Mr. Kang!

185
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:24,130
- How've you been?
- I waited so long for you.

186
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:27,800
She's Cats. Damn, I keep forgetting.

187
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,890
It's Cat Girl, sir.

188
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:33,800
Go on and introduce yourself, girl.

189
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:38,710
I'm Cat Girl. I promise
to sing my heart out.

190
00:12:38,710 --> 00:12:39,880
Thank you.

191
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:42,540
Of course you should.

192
00:12:42,810 --> 00:12:45,780
Let's go some place
quiet to talk, Mr. Kang.

193
00:12:45,780 --> 00:12:48,120
See you folks later.

194
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:52,920
- Come on, what are pals for.
- I can't.

195
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:56,860
It's just a show of my appreciation.

196
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,660
The album's finished?

197
00:12:58,660 --> 00:13:02,370
I put together all the
best songwriters around.

198
00:13:02,370 --> 00:13:05,600
You know me, I get what I want.

199
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:07,270
How is she?

200
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:10,780
Oh, her? Not bad.

201
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:14,780
But she has trouble getting
along with the others.

202
00:13:14,780 --> 00:13:17,120
Still she's got talent. Be nice.

203
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:20,710
Of course. Anything for you.

204
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:24,960
- But do this for me.
- I can't.

205
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,450
It's not much. Please, take it!

206
00:13:27,860 --> 00:13:34,700
I can't sleep at the thought of you.

207
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:40,070
My dear love.

208
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:47,580
That part you just sang. Try
not to scream it this time.

209
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:49,570
You'll scare 'em off.

210
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:53,210
How, sir?

211
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:59,920
How would you feel if someone
screamed they loved you?

212
00:14:00,230 --> 00:14:05,600
You know, softly and
tenderly? You're good at that.

213
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:10,290
What? Not that. Stop making me do it.

214
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:15,030
- That's not what I meant!
- Roll it!

215
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:26,420
What's she so good at?

216
00:14:26,850 --> 00:14:30,410
Drop it will ya, man?

217
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,850
Come on. Just between us?

218
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:42,300
She's my future. That's
all I can tell ya, man.

219
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:47,970
Did you fix the second verse?

220
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:49,570
What?

221
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:52,310
The climax on the second verse.

222
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,740
'AIways like yesterday'?

223
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:58,010
It's a little corny, isn't it?

224
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:02,910
'A world without love? ' How's that?

225
00:15:05,890 --> 00:15:08,920
Like that's not corny?

226
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:14,760
It's just a suggestion.

227
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:21,860
Let's not get too excited here.

228
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:29,510
You two write it, then. I'm out.

229
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,580
What?

230
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:37,820
So feisty.

231
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,580
Do you have to become a singer?

232
00:16:04,550 --> 00:16:06,070
What?

233
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:13,490
Got enough medication left?

234
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:31,170
My damn connection to your family.

235
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:38,510
First your father, now you.

236
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:43,410
There are too many illnesses
that can't be cured.

237
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:03,670
What's wrong?

238
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:10,040
What is it?

239
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:14,250
Don't cry.

240
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,780
Stop crying.

241
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:21,220
The bastards told me to rewrite it.

242
00:17:26,930 --> 00:17:30,920
'lf I could live again'.
How's that for the title?

243
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:34,070
'lf I could live again? '

244
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:40,070
If you could, what would
you like to be reborn as?

245
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:43,210
Besides a person?

246
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:45,940
Anything.

247
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:50,120
Well...

248
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:54,020
If I could live again...

249
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,260
A ring?

250
00:17:58,260 --> 00:17:59,660
Wait.

251
00:18:07,410 --> 00:18:09,000
Start over.

252
00:18:11,540 --> 00:18:13,740
If I could be born again...

253
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,310
A ring.

254
00:18:17,850 --> 00:18:19,410
A pair of glasses.

255
00:18:20,890 --> 00:18:22,550
A bed.

256
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:26,090
A diary.

257
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:29,730
Born again as things like
that? What fun is that?

258
00:18:29,730 --> 00:18:34,290
You can buy me. It'll
always be fun at your side.

259
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:38,070
So sensible.

260
00:18:38,970 --> 00:18:40,490
Did you eat?

261
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:42,400
Of course, I did.

262
00:18:43,410 --> 00:18:45,240
Well, I didn't.

263
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:49,180
Then let's eat.

264
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:56,590
Is there anything you want to tell me?

265
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:58,320
Like what?

266
00:18:58,660 --> 00:19:02,190
A deep, dark secret?

267
00:19:02,190 --> 00:19:06,460
Think of it as a confession
at a Catholic church.

268
00:19:07,570 --> 00:19:10,260
