at a time like this, right?

638
00:53:08,640 --> 00:53:12,970
Yell at you or something?

639
00:53:15,850 --> 00:53:24,050
Funny, somehow I feel a little grateful.

640
00:53:26,290 --> 00:53:28,380
I'm going out for a smoke.

641
00:53:31,760 --> 00:53:33,130
So uncomfortable.

642
00:53:37,170 --> 00:53:38,930
My engagement's off.

643
00:53:47,550 --> 00:53:49,950
I don't have parents.

644
00:53:52,880 --> 00:53:56,410
I was studying late at high
school in my senior year.

645
00:53:57,620 --> 00:54:01,020
My homeroom teacher came
in and stared right at me.

646
00:54:01,290 --> 00:54:10,000
Like someone who came
to take me on death row.

647
00:54:11,470 --> 00:54:14,060
Like in the movies, you know?

648
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:19,210
Anyway, he told me

649
00:54:19,480 --> 00:54:23,810
to go to the hospital right away.

650
00:54:24,150 --> 00:54:27,120
When I asked why...

651
00:54:27,350 --> 00:54:30,420
if he said my parents and

652
00:54:30,420 --> 00:54:33,860
sister died in a car accident...

653
00:54:34,390 --> 00:54:39,660
then I wouldn't have gone
and seen them like that.

654
00:54:41,570 --> 00:54:44,900
I see...

655
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:48,130
K's been with me ever since.

656
00:54:49,110 --> 00:54:50,570
K?

657
00:54:52,810 --> 00:54:56,910
You saw him, Producer KANG Chul-kyu?

658
00:54:57,750 --> 00:55:01,580
His name sounds too corny
so I just call him K.

659
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:09,590
At home, he's my Mom
At work, he's my Dad.

660
00:55:09,830 --> 00:55:12,020
